document.title: Physical Education Model Content Standards for California Public Schools, Kindergarten Through Grade Twelve

F7284D50DFE301318E8E68A86D17958E.description: Analyze possible solutions to a movement problem in a cooperative physical activity and come to a consensus on the best solution.

F7280C60DFE301318E8D68A86D17958E.description: Identify and agree on a common goal when participating in a cooperative physical activity.

F7278F60DFE301318E8B68A86D17958E.description: Identify and define the role of each participant in a cooperative physical activity.

F72711B0DFE301318E8968A86D17958E.description: Evaluate individual responsibility in group efforts.

F726CFC0DFE301318E8868A86D17958E.description: Participate productively in group physical activities.

F7264370DFE301318E8668A86D17958E.description: Students demonstrate and utilize knowledge of psychological and sociological concepts, principles, and strategies that apply to the learning and performance of physical activity.

F7260550DFE301318E8568A86D17958E.description: Compile and analyze a log noting the food intake/calories consumed and energy expended through physical activity.

F725C6A0DFE301318E8468A86D17958E.description: List the long-term benefits of participation in regular physical activity.

F72585F0DFE301318E8368A86D17958E.description: Explain methods of monitoring heart rate intensity

F7254330DFE301318E8268A86D17958E.description: Classify physical activities as aerobic or anaerobic.

F724FB00DFE301318E8168A86D17958E.description: Identify contraindicated exercises and their adverse effects on the body.

F724A210DFE301318E8068A86D17958E.description: Develop a one-day personal physical fitness plan specifying the intensity, time, and types of physical activities for each component of health-related physical fitness.

F72438C0DFE301318E7F68A86D17958E.description: Distinguish between effective and ineffective warm-up and cool-down techniques.

F723F030DFE301318E7E68A86D17958E.description: Students demonstrate knowledge of physical fitness concepts, principles, and strategies to improve health and performance.

F723AFE0DFE301318E7D68A86D17958E.description: Monitor the intensity of one's heart rate during physical activity.

F7236C90DFE301318E7C68A86D17958E.description: Measure and evaluate changes in health-related physical fitness based on physical activity patterns.

F7231510DFE301318E7B68A86D17958E.description: Participate in moderate to vigorous physical activity a minimum of four days each week.

F72295C0DFE301318E7A68A86D17958E.description: Develop individual goals for each of the components of health-related physical fitness (muscle strength, muscle endurance, flexibility, aerobic capacity, and body composition).

F7225550DFE301318E7968A86D17958E.description: Compare individual physical fitness results with research-based standards for good health.

F72213B0DFE301318E7868A86D17958E.description: Assess the components of health-related physical fitness (muscle strength, muscle endurance, flexibility, aerobic capacity, and body composition) by using a scientifically based health-related fitness assessment.

F721CE30DFE301318E7768A86D17958E.description: Students assess and maintain a level of physical fitness to improve health and performance.

F7218670DFE301318E7668A86D17958E.description: Develop a cooperative movement game that uses locomotor skills, object manipulation, and an offensive strategy and teach the game to another person.

F7213FE0DFE301318E7568A86D17958E.description: Combination of Movement Patterns and Skills

F720F6F0DFE301318E7468A86D17958E.description: Explain how movement qualities contribute to the aesthetic dimension of physical activity.

F720B4B0DFE301318E7368A86D17958E.description: Identify steps and rhythm patterns for folk and line dances.

F7202C70DFE301318E7168A86D17958E.description: Identify opportunities to pass or dribble while being guarded.

F71FE360DFE301318E7068A86D17958E.description: Illustrate how the intended direction of an object is affected by the angle of the implement or body part at the time of contact.

F71F8DD0DFE301318E6F68A86D17958E.description: Identify the time necessary to prepare for and begin a forehand stroke and a backhand stroke.

F71F38D0DFE301318E6E68A86D17958E.description: Explain the role of the legs, shoulders, and forearm in the forearm pass.

F71EAC00DFE301318E6C68A86D17958E.description: Identify practices and procedures necessary for safe participation in physical activities.

F71E6790DFE301318E6B68A86D17958E.description: Provide feedback to a partner to assist in developing and improving movement skills.

F71E23A0DFE301318E6A68A86D17958E.description: Analyze and correct errors in movement patterns.

F71DDAB0DFE301318E6968A86D17958E.description: Explain how impact force is reduced by increasing the duration of impact.

F71D8F50DFE301318E6868A86D17958E.description: Explain how to increase force based on the principles of biomechanics.

F71D0050DFE301318E6668A86D17958E.description: Students demonstrate knowledge of movement concepts, principles, and strategies that apply to the learning and performance of physical activities.

F71C7590DFE301318E6468A86D17958E.description: Design and perform smooth, flowing sequences of stunts, tumbling, and rhythmic patterns that combine traveling, rolling, balancing, and transferring weight.

F71C3390DFE301318E6368A86D17958E.description: Combine motor skills to play a lead-up or modified game.

F71CBAF0DFE301318E6568A86D17958E.description: Combine relationships, levels, speed, direction, and pathways in complex individual and group physical activities.

F71BE5C0DFE301318E6268A86D17958E.description: Combinations of Movement Patterns and Skills

F71BA0C0DFE301318E6168A86D17958E.description: Develop, refine, and demonstrate routines to music.

F71AAEF0DFE301318E5E68A86D17958E.description: Throw an object accurately and with applied force, using the underhand, overhand, and sidearm movement (throw) patterns.

F71A5E20DFE301318E5D68A86D17958E.description: Dribble and pass a ball to a partner while being guarded.

F71A0B50DFE301318E5C68A86D17958E.description: Strike an object consistently, using an implement, so that the object travels in the intended direction at the desired height.

F719C6D0DFE301318E5B68A86D17958E.description: Strike an object consistently, using a body part, so that the object travels in the intended direction at the desired height.

F7198A00DFE301318E5A68A86D17958E.description: Strike a ball continuously against a wall and with a partner, using a paddle for the forehand stroke and the backhand stroke.

F7194C90DFE301318E5968A86D17958E.description: Volley an object repeatedly with a partner, using the forearm pass.

F718BEF0DFE301318E5768A86D17958E.description: Students demonstrate the motor skills and movement patterns needed to perform a variety of physical activities.
